<figureCitation box="[743,845,335,361]" captionStart-0="Fig" captionStart-1="Fig" captionStartId-0="10.[188,232,1963,1989]" captionStartId-1="11.[190,233,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox-0="[189,1398,1238,1924]" captionTargetBox-1="[193,1383,550,1865]" captionTargetId-0="figure-248@10.[189,1398,1238,1924]" captionTargetId-1="figure-69@11.[189,1398,543,1890]" captionTargetPageId-0="10" captionTargetPageId-1="11" captionText-0="Fig. 2. Distribution map showing the type localities of Quedius gissaricus sp. nov. (red circle) and Q. viator sp. nov. (violet circle)." captionText-1="Fig. 3. Quedius viator sp. nov., holotype (ZIN). A. Habitus. B–D. Aedeagus. B. From parameral side. C. Apical portion of paramere (underside). D. Lateral view. E. Sternite VIII. F. Tegite X. G. Sternite IX. Scale bars: A = 1 mm; B–G = 0.5 mm.." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6658771" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6658773" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6658771/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6658773/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="151">Figs 2–3</figureCitation>
